<TITLE> ICDDR, B opens new diarrhoea centre in Mirpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 30 (bdnews24.com)The International Centre for Diarrhoeal Diseases Research on Thursday set up a temporary diarrhoea treatment centre in Mirpur to ease the load on its headquarters on Mohakhali in the capital. ICDDR,B spokesman Ishtiaque A Zaman said the centre would treat the patients from the area since one in every six to seven patients is coming to its Mohakhali premises from Mirpur. Some 800 diarrhoea patients visit the ICDDR, B's Mohakhali centre every day. Zaman said the makeshift centre has been set up on the ground floor of the Unani and Ayurvedic Degree College and Hospital campus at Mirpur-13. He said the centre was opened to patients after health minister A F M Ruhul Haque inaugurated it Thursday evening. To draw the attention of the Mirpur residents, Zaman said, they would announce the news of the new centre through loudspeakers in the neighbourhoods.
